# Basic Japanese Vocabulary

Welcome to the "Basic Japanese Vocabulary" guide! In this guide, we'll cover essential Japanese words and phrases that are commonly used in everyday conversation. Whether you're a beginner or looking to refresh your Japanese skills, mastering these basic vocabulary words will help you communicate more effectively in Japanese. Let's get started!

## Greetings and Expressions

1. **Konnichiwa (こんにちは)** - Hello / Good afternoon
2. **Ohayou gozaimasu (おはようございます)** - Good morning
3. **Konbanwa (こんばんは)** - Good evening
4. **Arigatou (ありがとう)** - Thank you
5. **Sumimasen (すみません)** - Excuse me / I'm sorry

## Numbers

6. **Ichi (いち)** - One
7. **Ni (に)** - Two
8. **San (さん)** - Three
9. **Yon / Shi (よん / し)** - Four
10. **Go (ご)** - Five

## Colors

11. **Aka (あか)** - Red
12. **Ao (あお)** - Blue
13. **Midori (みどり)** - Green
14. **Kiiro (きいろ)** - Yellow
15. **Shiro (しろ)** - White

## Basic Phrases

16. **Watashi wa ____ desu (わたしは ____ です)** - I am ____
17. **O-genki desu ka? (おげんき ですか)** - How are you?
18. **Namae wa nan desu ka? (なまえは なん です か)** - What is your name?
19. **Eigo ga hanasemasu ka? (えいご が はなせます か)** - Can you speak English?
20. **Doko desu ka? (どこ です か)** - Where is it?

## Food and Drink

21. **Sushi (すし)** - Sushi
22. **Ramen (らーめん)** - Ramen noodles
23. **Ocha (おちゃ)** - Tea
24. **Kohi (こうひ)** - Coffee
25. **Mizu (みず)** - Water

## Common Objects

26. **Terebi (てれび)** - Television
27. **Denwa (でんわ)** - Telephone
28. **Kasa (かさ)** - Umbrella
29. **Kagi (かぎ)** - Key
30. **Kaban (かばん)** - Bag

## Places

31. **Gakkou (がっこう)** - School
32. **Ie (いえ)** - House / Home
33. **Resutoran (れすとらん)** - Restaurant
34. **Kouen (こうえん)** - Park
35. **Eki (えき)** - Train station

## Emotions

36. **Ureshii (うれしい)** - Happy
37. **Kanashii (かなしい)** - Sad
38. **Kowai (こわい)** - Scared
39. **Genki (げんき)** - Energetic / Healthy
40. **Okotta (おこった)** - Angry

## Time and Days

41. **Jikan (じかん)** - Time
42. **Getsuyoubi (げつようび)** - Monday
43. **Kayoubi (かようび)** - Tuesday
44. **Suiyoubi (すいようび)** - Wednesday
45. **Mokuyoubi (もくようび)** - Thursday

## Family

46. **Otousan (おとうさん)** - Father / Dad
47. **Okaasan (おかあさん)** - Mother / Mom
48. **Oniisan (おにいさん)** - Older brother
49. **Oneesan (おねえさん)** - Older sister
50. **Imouto (いもうと)** - Younger sister

## Conclusion

Congratulations on learning some basic Japanese vocabulary! Practice using these words and phrases in your daily life to improve your Japanese language skills. Remember to keep practicing and expanding your vocabulary to become more proficient in Japanese. Ganbatte kudasai (がんばって ください) - Good luck!

